UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2277
1 (2) The court shall consider any motion filed in accordance with subsection (1) of this
2 section within sixty (60) days of the filing date of that motion, and shall enter its
3 ruling within ten (10) days after considering the motion. The defendant may, in the
4 discretion of the trial court, have the right to a hearing on any motion he or she may
5 file, or have filed for him or her, that would suspend further execution of sentence.
6 Any court order granting or denying a motion to suspend further execution of
7 sentence is not reviewable.
8 (3) (a) During the period in which the defendant may file a motion pursuant to this
9 statute, the sentencing judge, within his or her discretion, may order that the
10 defendant be held in a local detention facility that is not at or above maximum
11 capacity until such time as the court rules on said motion. During this period
12 of detention, and prior to the court's ruling on said motion, the court may
13 require the defendant to participate in any approved community work program
14 or other forms of work release. Persons held in the county jail pursuant to this
15 subsection shall not be subject to transfer to a state correctional facility until
16 the decision is made not to place the petitioner on shock probation.
17 (b) The provisions concerning community work programs or other forms of work
18 release shall apply only to persons convicted of Class C or Class D felonies,
19 and may be granted only after a hearing at which the Commonwealth's
20 attorney has the opportunity to present arguments in favor or opposition
21 thereto.
22 (4) (a) If the defendant is a violent offender as defined in KRS 439.3401, the
23 sentence shall not be probated under this section.[
24 (b) The sentence shall not be probated under this section if the defendant has been
25 convicted of [:
26 1. ]a violation of either KRS 507.040 or 507.050[507A.040] and a
27 violation of KRS 189A.010 arising out of the same incident[; or
