1 2. A violation of either KRS 507.050 or 507A.050 and a violation of KRS
2 189A.010 arising out of the same incident].
3 (5) If the defendant has been convicted of an offense under KRS 510.050, 510.080,
4 530.020, 530.064(1)(a), or 531.310, or criminal attempt to commit any of these
5 offenses under KRS 506.010, the sentence shall not be suspended, in accordance
6 with KRS 532.045.
7 (6) When a defendant has been convicted of a sex crime, as defined in KRS 17.500, the
8 court shall order a comprehensive sex offender presentence evaluation, unless one
9 has been provided within the past six (6) months, in which case the court may order
10 an update of the comprehensive sex offender presentence evaluation of the
11 defendant conducted by the sex offender treatment program operated or approved
12 by the Department of Corrections or the Sex Offender Risk Assessment Advisory
13 Board. The comprehensive sex offender presentence evaluation shall provide to the
14 court a recommendation related to the risk of a repeat offense by the defendant and
15 the defendant's amenability to treatment, and shall be considered by the court in
16 determining whether to suspend the sentence. If the court suspends the sentence and
17 places the defendant on probation, the provisions of KRS 532.045(3) to (7) shall
18 apply.
19 (7) The authority granted in this section shall be exercised by the judge who imposed
20 sentence on the defendant, unless he or she is unable to act and it appears that his or
21 her inability to act should continue beyond the expiration of the term of the court.
22 In such case, the judge who imposed sentence shall assign a judge to dispose of a
23 motion filed under this section, or as prescribed by the rules and practices
24 concerning the responsibility for disposition of criminal matters.
25 (8) The provisions of this section shall not apply where a sentence of death has been
26 imposed.
27 Section 9. The following KRS sections are repealed:
Page 5 of 6
XXXX 2/23/2026 6:25 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2277
1 507A.010 Definitions -- Exceptions.
2 507A.020 Fetal homicide in the first degree.
3 507A.030 Fetal homicide in the second degree.
4 507A.040 Fetal homicide in the third degree.
5 507A.050 Fetal homicide in the fourth degree.
6 507A.060 Death sentence prohibited.
7 Section 10. The changes in law made by this Act apply only to conduct that
8 occurs on or after the effective date of this Act. Conduct that occurs before the effective
9 date of this Act is governed by the law in effect at the time the conduct occurred, and that
10 law is continued in effect for that purpose.
11 Section 11. Existing provisions relating to prenatal homicide or assault or
12 regulating abortion or abortion facilities are not repealed but are superseded to the extent
13 that those provisions may conflict with or may be inconsistent with Section 1, 2, 3, 4, 5,
14 6, or 7 of this Act.
15 Section 12. This Act may be cited as the Prenatal Equal Protection Act.
